==When  to link==
Adding links to an article makes it more useful, but too many links can be distracting. To avoid [[WP:Overlink|overlinking]], you should normally create a link in an article only at the ''first occurrence'' of a word or phrase (thus, lead sections of articles often have more links than other sections).  You should not link common words such as "state" and "world", even though Wikipedia has articles for those words, unless these common words are central concepts to the article.

